articles.author: The Associated Press
articles.title: Diane Keaton, Oscar-winning star of 'Annie Hall' and 'The Godfather,' dies at 79 - NPR
articles.description: The actor, known for her quirky, vibrant manner and depth was 79. Across her decades-long career, she worked with prominent filmmakers including Francis Ford Coppola, Woody Allen and Nancy Meyers.
articles.content: Diane Keaton, the Oscar-winning star of "Annie Hall," "The Godfather" films and "Father of the Bride," whose quirky, vibrant manner and depth made her one of the most singular actors of a generation,… [+8738 chars]
